And in that, one of the panels, decomposing like a drawing harmonica, as a result of a cable clenching, was damaged on an area of nearly one meter.
The decomposition has been suspended to prevent further damage to the panel.
Astronauts who were originally supposed to perform a control output on the Discovery ship and then go to fix another solar panel whose rotation system was malfunctioning were forced to devote themselves to the damaged panel.
