The tools he used, namely a mini stick coated with an insulating device to prevent electroshock on the solar panels producing several hundred volts, were invented and "produced" by astronauts on board the station.
After the operation, Scott Parazynski waited for the panel to be completely decomposed and then infiltrated his tools and returned to the inner part of the station.
