What insurance is suitable for me?
The insurance of a car which protects the driver in the event of an accident is a significant expense, depending on different factors such as age, condition, sex, length of possession of a driving licence, type of vehicle to be insured or used, etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
It is even more difficult to choose suitable car insurance than to choose a model car.
First of all, we need to be clear about what we're talking about.
The insurance of a car is an agreement between an insurance company and an insurance company.
This commitment takes the form of an insurance contract which provides that the insurance undertaking will receive an agreed insurance premium of a certain amount for taking charge of the claims in the event of an insurance event.
Insurance is the price of insurance which is determined taking into account various factors such as age, condition, sex, length of licence holding, type of vehicle that is insured or used, etc.
Insurance companies set their prices on the basis of statistics, so the higher the probability of an accident, the higher the premium rate.
For this reason, both persons over 25 and women must pay lower premiums, as statistics show that they have a lower risk index due to their caution.
In the same way, on the basis of the checks, insurance companies concluded that married persons have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The way the vehicle is used will affect the frequency of journeys and thus the likelihood of an accident.
The increase in the rate of rides increases the probability.
There are many variables that insurance companies consider when setting the price of insurance premiums.
Therefore, the driver must study the situation well in order to choose the insurance that best fits his insurance profile.
We will show here the most important variables for the selection of one or the other type of insurance, which, in addition to complying with the type of insured person, will also be at a reasonable price.
People under the age of 25 face various disadvantages such as lack of experience in driving and short possession of a driving licence when they want to negotiate insurance premiums at an affordable price.
Although ideal for good coverage is insurance against all risks, there are also cheaper options.
The most cautious drivers can choose insurance against all risks at a discount in order to obtain insurance cover for all risks, but at a more affordable price.
This type of contract would assume the client's involvement in the payment of the insurance claim.
"The part of the premium payment provided by the client will be determined in advance when determining the price of the premium, which would be the lower of the participation ', explains Luis Noguera, the main head of First Europe in Spain, the Internet insurance intermediary.
Another option is insurance extended to other participants in the operation by ensuring that the client is insured against damage caused to other persons, but not against damage to his own car.
In addition, he would be insured against theft, fire and loss of vehicle.
Recommendations.
If you're under 25, try to be attentive and avoid accidents as much as possible, because it will affect your bonus and allow you to reduce insurance premiums in the future.
A bonus is a reduction in the basic rate of the insurance company.
On the other hand, the malus is an increase in that basic rate.
"Bonus and malus will depend on the insurance company and its profits.
If the insurance company had a good year, it would be able to afford to raise the bonus, "explains Noguera.
After crossing the 25-year limit, drivers get easier when they go to arrange insurance, because the client's risk index decreases because of experience gained.
For this reason, it is most recommended to negotiate insurance against all risks at a discount.
"Young people are usually unable to make use of the experience acquired in advance when an accident occurs and even when driving," the director of a European company in Spain assures, and adds that most accidents occur in the second year of the procedure, when the "fear of a newcomer" has already been overcome.
However, if the client is married but has no children, it is better to arrange insurance against all risks, if the economic situation permits.
Families with children are considered by insurance companies to be the clients with the lowest risk index and thus their premiums will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be insurance against all risks at a discount (which could be EUR 300) or with a high bonus, insurance extended to other traffic participants, starting from the third year after the purchase of the vehicle.
"Their management is calmer and their purchasing capacity is higher, so they can afford luxury to get the highest discount," says Luis Noguer.
Retirement insurance against all risks at a discount of EUR 150 is recommended, or insurance extended to other participants in the operation, provided that a high bonus has been achieved.
It must be said that car insurance is something important not only because it protects the driver in the event of an accident, but also because it represents a considerable expense, which is a valid reason to study the insurance options that would suit us most in the face of our personal situation.
