Previous events are a tangled, confusing chain of artistic and curator events.
Warhol made his first Brillo boxes in New York in 1964, painted wooden boxes that were based on the red and blue-white design of paper boxes of soap powder Brillo.
The exhibition of his works at Moderna Museet in 1968 showed - with Warhol's consent - hundreds of Brillo boxes from a cardboard box. They did not come (for financial reasons) from Warhol, but were delivered directly from the Brillo factory.
